day hew to the principles Jesus articulated? How can justice be pursued in the context of competing national narratives and historical understandings? What bearing do or should centuries of Christian violence against Jews and Muslims have on contemporary theology and ethics? Is it ethical, or even possible, to set aside millennia of Christian anti-Semitism in judging Israel’s conduct? What Christian values should be honored in pursuing Jesus’s mission of reconciliation today? How may the pursuit of truth be corrupted by passionate social witness? Can advocacy cross the line into hatred? These are among the critical questions this collection poses and attempts to address.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aArab-Israeli conflictxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aBoycott, divestment, and sanctions movementxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 7aRELIGION / Religious Intolerance, Persecution & Conflict.2bisacsh  aBDS.  aBoycott-Divestment-Sanctions.  aInterfaith Relations.  aIsraeli-Arab.  aIsraeli-Palestinian.  aJudaism and Christianity.  aZionism.  aantisemitism.1 aAndrews, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aC. Gizzi, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCathey, Robert A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFox Sandmel, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedman, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGizzi, Michael C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarter, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKampen, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKessler, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relat